caption: This place is fantastic. I love their burgers. I especially love their Italian Ice. They’re significantly better than Mario’s in every way and nobody can change my mind. The watermelon Italian ice is to die for.

I got the 1/3 cheeseburger Andrew fries. You probably got 1-1/2 to 2 cups of fries. And the burger was a pretty hefty size too. Not bad for ~$9! Great service, great taste. This definitely hit the spot. Will be my new place to go if I ever need something quick!

This place is a gem, on a quiet neighborhood corner. Just outside the ring of expensive restaurants near downtown, the prices are very reasonable. I had the steak burrito, and it was so delicious. Very filling. I will be returning here for sure.

They charged me $8.59 for a veggie burger and guess what! No bill!! The last time I had been here with a friend, it was 6.59 for the same parcel. Also, they asked to pay extra 50 cents for sauce. Most shocking thing is they did not give me a bill!

The beef is great, and so is the Italian ice. The fries have a particularly nice crunch. Awesome owners. There’s ample outdoor seating for pandemic dining. This is a great place for such a quiet unassuming corner.

The Steak Sandwich with French Fries is amazing. The steak is extremely fresh and well seasoned. The French Fries are made fresh to order and are perfect. The selection on the menu is very complete with each item made fresh to order with exceptionally high quality products. The service is very prompt friendly and knowledgeable. The place has been open for decades and continues to improve with time. It is a Fine place to stop by before a game or event at the UIC Pavilion. The restranunt is within walking distance of the university. Attend!!!

Great local joint with a long family history. If you believe in supporting local come here. This joint is still run by the family 3 generations later. The Italian beef was good but has a different spice than you might expect, I could not identify it. There also is not much of the oreagano spice. The  is giardiniera is homemade and has jalepenos, not bad, just different. The Italian ice is really good, had the lemon. Definantley the start of the stop. Warning though, call ahead to be sure they are open. They closed an hour earlier than posted on the internet and they have no times posted on the door.
